{
  "type": "USJ",
  "version": "3.1",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "book",
      "marker": "id",
      "code": "MRK",
      "content": [
        "- Good News Study Bible - Notes Material"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "chapter",
      "marker": "c",
      "number": "1",
      "sid": "MRK 1"
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "p",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "1",
          "sid": "MRK 1:1"
        },
        "This is the Good News about Jesus Christ, the Son of God",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.1: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "the Son of God: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Not included in some manuscripts."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        ".",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.1 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Some manuscripts do not have "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "the Son of God."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "2",
          "sid": "MRK 1:2"
        },
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.2: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fk",
              "content": [
                "Prophet"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        "It began as the prophet Isaiah had written",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.2: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "Isaiah had written: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "The quotation in 1.2 is from Mal 3.1; “ahead of you” may be from Ex 23.20, “Someone is shouting in the desert, ‘Get the road ready for the Lord; make a straight path for our God to travel!’ ”."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        ":",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "x",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "xo",
              "content": [
                "1.2: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "xt",
              "content": [
                "Mal 3.1"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        "“God said, ‘I will send my messenger ahead of you"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "to clear the way for you.’"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q1",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "3",
          "sid": "MRK 1:3"
        },
        "Someone is shouting in the desert,",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "x",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "xo",
              "content": [
                "1.3: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "xt",
              "content": [
                "Is 40.3 (LXX)"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "‘Get the road ready for the Lord;"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "q2",
      "content": [
        "make a straight path for him to travel",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.3: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "someone is…travel: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "is from Is 40.3, following Septuagint; the Hebrew means, “Get the road ready in the desert”."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        "!’”"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "para",
      "marker": "p",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "4",
          "sid": "MRK 1:4"
        },
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.4: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fk",
              "content": [
                "Baptizing"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        "So John appeared",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.4: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "John appeared: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "John probably began his ministry in AD 27 (Lk 3.1-3)."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        " in the desert",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.4: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "the desert: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "The desolate region on the west side of the River Jordan, not far from where it empties into the Dead Sea."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        ", baptizing and preaching.",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "f",
          "caller": "+",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.4 "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "John appeared in the desert, baptizing and preaching; "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "some manuscripts have "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "John the Baptist appeared in the desert, preaching."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.4: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "John…baptizing and preaching: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "Some manuscripts have “John the Baptist appeared in the desert, preaching”."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        " “Turn away from your sins and be baptized,” he told the people, “and God will forgive your sins.” ",
        {
          "type": "verse",
          "marker": "v",
          "number": "5",
          "sid": "MRK 1:5"
        },
        "Many people from the province of Judea",
        {
          "type": "note",
          "marker": "ef",
          "caller": "-",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fr",
              "content": [
                "1.5: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "fq",
              "content": [
                "Judea: "
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "char",
              "marker": "ft",
              "content": [
                "One of the provinces, in the south, into which the land of Israel was then divided."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        " and the city of Jerusalem went out to hear John. They confessed their sins, and he baptized them in the River Jordan. ..."
      ]
    }
  ]
}